1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
Not all conversation is gossip.

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:07,440
Bull sessions, shop talk, and just batting the breeze are necessary at times.

3
00:00:07,630 --> 00:00:10,480
They serve a good purpose when they are constructive.

4
00:00:10,670 --> 00:00:14,960
You can test your proneness to be a gossiper by taking this test.

5
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:17,279
1.

6
00:00:17,630 --> 00:00:20,319
Do I spread rumors about other people?

7
00:00:20,319 --> 00:00:21,200
2.

8
00:00:21,470 --> 00:00:24,559
Do I always have good things to say about others?

9
00:00:24,559 --> 00:00:25,520
3.

10
00:00:25,870 --> 00:00:28,799
Do I like to hear reports of a scandal?

11
00:00:28,799 --> 00:00:29,680
4.

12
00:00:29,950 --> 00:00:33,279
Do I judge others only on the basis of facts?

13
00:00:33,279 --> 00:00:34,400
5.

14
00:00:34,750 --> 00:00:38,079
Do I encourage others to bring their rumors to me?

15
00:00:38,590 --> 00:00:39,279
6.

16
00:00:39,550 --> 00:00:43,920
Do I proceed my conversations with, don't tell anybody?

17
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:45,039
7.

18
00:00:45,150 --> 00:00:48,559
Do I keep confidential information confidential?

19
00:00:48,910 --> 00:00:49,520
8.

20
00:00:49,789 --> 00:00:54,160
Do I feel guilty about what I say concerning other people?

21
00:00:56,190 --> 00:00:58,000
The right answers are obvious.

22
00:00:59,150 --> 00:01:01,520
Meditate on this thought for just a moment.

23
00:01:01,710 --> 00:01:08,400
Taking an axe and chopping your neighbor's furniture to pieces won't make your furniture look one bit better.

24
00:01:08,590 --> 00:01:17,520
And using verbal axes and grenades on another person doesn't do one thing to make you a better you or me a better me.

25
00:01:19,470 --> 00:01:21,039
Go first class.

26
00:01:21,070 --> 00:01:27,520
That is an excellent rule to follow in everything you do, including the goods and services you buy.

27
00:01:27,949 --> 00:01:39,760
Once, to prove the unconditional truth of the go-first-class thinking, I asked a group of trainees to give one example of how they had been penny-wise and pound-foolish.

28
00:01:40,109 --> 00:01:42,400
Here are some sample replies.

29
00:01:42,829 --> 00:01:46,000
I bought a low-priced suit from an offbeat retailer.

30
00:01:46,029 --> 00:01:49,760
Thought I got a bargain, but the suit was simply no good.

31
00:01:50,509 --> 00:01:53,360
My car needed a new automatic transmission.

32
00:01:53,389 --> 00:01:59,760
Took it to an alley garage that agreed to do the job for $25 less than an authorized dealer.

33
00:02:00,109 --> 00:02:06,320
The new transmission lasted 1,800 miles, and the garage wouldn't make it right.

34
00:02:06,909 --> 00:02:10,880
For months, I ate at a real greasy spoon trying to save money.

35
00:02:10,989 --> 00:02:15,280
The place wasn't clean, the food wasn't good, the service, well,

36
00:02:15,309 --> 00:02:20,079
you couldn't call it that, and the clientele was a bunch of downed healers.

37
00:02:20,509 --> 00:02:25,760
One day, a friend persuaded me to join him for lunch at one of the best restaurants in town.

38
00:02:25,869 --> 00:02:29,360
He ordered the businessman's lunch, so I did too.

39
00:02:29,549 --> 00:02:31,440
I was amazed at what I got.

40
00:02:31,629 --> 00:02:38,480
Good food, good service, good atmosphere, and for just a little more than I had been paying at the Greasy Spoon.
